<h1>About Info</h1>
<h2>Sandra Mashin is a psychologist and teacher who has worked in the education field for twenty years. Her passion for students learning a collection of effective writing skills reflects her research as well. She has devised a unique easy to understand writing program that aims to make learning to write essays, short stories, grammar, sentence construction, vocabulary, handwriting and rhetoric. Working as a principal, department head and tutor provided her with a wealth of insight into the needs of students and parents. Sandra also specializes in a range of exceptional students, gifted and students with learning disabilities, utilizing powerful learning strategies. Her goal is to provide the language skills that are no longer taught in elementary and high schools so that students can build successful dreams to enter post secondary schools and careers of their choice. Her program is for all students.</h2>
